= ackack

http://www.github.com/mccraigmccraig/ackack

== DESCRIPTION:

an integration of ack [ http://code.google.com/p/ack/ ] into emacs + ecb

== FEATURES:

- use ack from emacs to search file hierarchies
- sensitive to ecb source paths to search current project
- results are clickable

== PROBLEMS:

- none

== SYNOPSIS:

M-x ack   : ack for a pattern from the top level of the enclosing ecb source path
M-x ack1  : ack for a pattern from one level down towards the current file from the enclosing ecb source path
M-x ack2  : ack for a pattern from two levels down towards the current file from the enclosin ecb source path

== REQUIREMENTS:

Emacs

== INSTALL:

;; add to your .emacs
(setq load-path (append '("~/path/to/ackack") load-path))
(require 'ackack)

